Package com.cs546.backend.core.city

Class CityData

java.lang.Object
com.cs546.backend.core.city.CityData
public class CityData
extends java.lang.Object
This class makes use of the builder pattern alongside the CityDataBuilder class. The purpose of using the builder pattern here is that the front end displays data about the city. The front end is written in Angular and thus needs the data to be replicated in the same easy to read format from backend to frontend for it to parse it properly. Instead of creating multiple different objects to group together pollution, traffic, city statistics and the number of businesses, houses and retail units, and send them via get requests to the front end, using builder pattern affords the ability to use a single large constructor to achieve the same goals from 1 get request call.
